48 class Debug::TemporaryObjectsTracker : public HeapObjectAllocationTracker {
49  public:
50  TemporaryObjectsTracker() = default;
51  ~TemporaryObjectsTracker() override = default;
52  TemporaryObjectsTracker(const TemporaryObjectsTracker&) = delete;
53  TemporaryObjectsTracker& operator=(const TemporaryObjectsTracker&) = delete;
54 
55  void AllocationEvent(Address addr, int size) override {
56  if (disabled) return;
57  AddRegion(addr, addr + size);
58  }
59 
60  void MoveEvent(Address from, Address to, int size) override {
61  if (from == to) return;
62  base::MutexGuard guard(&mutex_);
63  if (RemoveFromRegions(from, from + size)) {
64  // We had the object tracked as temporary, so we will track the
65  // new location as temporary, too.
66  AddRegion(to, to + size);
67  } else {
68  // The object we moved is a non-temporary, so the new location is also
69  // non-temporary. Thus we remove everything we track there (because it
70  // must have become dead).
71  RemoveFromRegions(to, to + size);
72  }
73  }
74 
75  bool HasObject(DirectHandle<HeapObject> obj) {
76  if (IsJSObject(*obj) && Cast<JSObject>(obj)->GetEmbedderFieldCount()) {
77  // Embedder may store any pointers using embedder fields and implements
78  // non trivial logic, e.g. create wrappers lazily and store pointer to
79  // native object inside embedder field. We should consider all objects
80  // with embedder fields as non temporary.
81  return false;
82  }
83  Address addr = obj->address();
84  return HasRegionContainingObject(addr, addr + obj->Size());
85  }
86 
87  bool disabled = false;
88 
89  private:
90  bool HasRegionContainingObject(Address start, Address end) {
91  // Check if there is a region that contains (overlaps) this object's space.
92  auto it = FindOverlappingRegion(start, end, false);
93  // If there is, we expect the region to contain the entire object.
94  DCHECK_IMPLIES(it != regions_.end(),
95  it->second <= start && end <= it->first);
96  return it != regions_.end();
97  }
98 
99  // This function returns any one of the overlapping regions (there might be
100  // multiple). If {include_adjacent} is true, it will also consider regions
101  // that have no overlap but are directly connected.
102  std::map<Address, Address>::iterator FindOverlappingRegion(
103  Address start, Address end, bool include_adjacent) {
104  // Region A = [start, end) overlaps with an existing region [existing_start,
105  // existing_end) iff (start <= existing_end) && (existing_start <= end).
106  // Since we index {regions_} by end address, we can find a candidate that
107  // satisfies the first condition using lower_bound.
108  if (include_adjacent) {
109  auto it = regions_.lower_bound(start);
110  if (it == regions_.end()) return regions_.end();
111  if (it->second <= end) return it;
112  } else {
113  auto it = regions_.upper_bound(start);
114  if (it == regions_.end()) return regions_.end();
115  if (it->second < end) return it;
116  }
117  return regions_.end();
118  }
119 
120  void AddRegion(Address start, Address end) {
121  DCHECK_LT(start, end);
122 
123  // Region [start, end) can be combined with an existing region if they
124  // overlap.
125  while (true) {
126  auto it = FindOverlappingRegion(start, end, true);
127  // If there is no such region, we don't need to merge anything.
128  if (it == regions_.end()) break;
129 
130  // Otherwise, we found an overlapping region. We remove the old one and
131  // add the new region recursively (to handle cases where the new region
132  // overlaps multiple existing ones).
133  start = std::min(start, it->second);
134  end = std::max(end, it->first);
135  regions_.erase(it);
136  }
137 
138  // Add the new (possibly combined) region.
139  regions_.emplace(end, start);
140  }
141 
142  bool RemoveFromRegions(Address start, Address end) {
143  // Check if we have anything that overlaps with [start, end).
144  auto it = FindOverlappingRegion(start, end, false);
145  if (it == regions_.end()) return false;
146 
147  // We need to update all overlapping regions.
148  for (; it != regions_.end();
149  it = FindOverlappingRegion(start, end, false)) {
150  Address existing_start = it->second;
151  Address existing_end = it->first;
152  // If we remove the region [start, end) from an existing region
153  // [existing_start, existing_end), there can be at most 2 regions left:
154  regions_.erase(it);
155  // The one before {start} is: [existing_start, start)
156  if (existing_start < start) AddRegion(existing_start, start);
157  // And the one after {end} is: [end, existing_end)
158  if (end < existing_end) AddRegion(end, existing_end);
159  }
160  return true;
161  }
162 
163  // Tracking addresses is not enough, because a single allocation may combine
164  // multiple objects due to allocation folding. We track both start and end
165  // (exclusive) address of regions. We index by end address for faster lookup.
166  // Map: end address => start address
167  std::map<Address, Address> regions_;
168  base::Mutex mutex_;
169 };

189  JavaScriptFrame* frame) {

206 MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArray> Debug::CheckBreakPointsForLocations(
207  Handle<DebugInfo> debug_info, std::vector<BreakLocation>& break_locations,
208  bool* has_break_points) {
209  DirectHandle<FixedArray> break_points_hit =
210  isolate_->factory()->NewFixedArray(
211  debug_info->GetBreakPointCount(isolate_));
212  int break_points_hit_count = 0;
213  bool has_break_points_at_all = false;
214  for (size_t i = 0; i < break_locations.size(); i++) {
215  bool location_has_break_points;
216  MaybeDirectHandle<FixedArray> check_result = CheckBreakPoints(
217  debug_info, &break_locations[i], &location_has_break_points);
218  has_break_points_at_all |= location_has_break_points;
219  if (!check_result.is_null()) {
220  DirectHandle<FixedArray> break_points_current_hit =
221  check_result.ToHandleChecked();
222  int num_objects = break_points_current_hit->length();
223  for (int j = 0; j < num_objects; ++j) {
224  break_points_hit->set(break_points_hit_count++,
225  break_points_current_hit->get(j));
226  }
227  }
228  }
229  *has_break_points = has_break_points_at_all;
230  if (break_points_hit_count == 0) return {};
231 
232  break_points_hit->RightTrim(isolate_, break_points_hit_count);
233  return break_points_hit;
234 }

236 void BreakLocation::AllAtCurrentStatement(
237  Handle<DebugInfo> debug_info, JavaScriptFrame* frame,
238  std::vector<BreakLocation>* result_out) {
239  DCHECK(!debug_info->CanBreakAtEntry());
240  auto summary = FrameSummary::GetTop(frame).AsJavaScript();
241  int offset = summary.code_offset();
242  DirectHandle<AbstractCode> abstract_code = summary.abstract_code();
243  PtrComprCageBase cage_base = GetPtrComprCageBase(*debug_info);
244  if (IsCode(*abstract_code, cage_base)) offset = offset - 1;
245  int statement_position;
246  {
247  BreakIterator it(debug_info);
248  it.SkipTo(BreakIndexFromCodeOffset(debug_info, abstract_code, offset));
249  statement_position = it.statement_position();
250  }
251  for (BreakIterator it(debug_info); !it.Done(); it.Next()) {
252  if (it.statement_position() == statement_position) {
253  result_out->push_back(it.GetBreakLocation());
254  }
255  }
256 }

270 int BreakLocation::BreakIndexFromCodeOffset(
271  Handle<DebugInfo> debug_info, DirectHandle<AbstractCode> abstract_code,
272  int offset) {
273  // Run through all break points to locate the one closest to the address.
274  int closest_break = 0;
275  int distance = kMaxInt;
276  DCHECK(kFunctionEntryBytecodeOffset <= offset &&
277  offset < abstract_code->Size());
278  for (BreakIterator it(debug_info); !it.Done(); it.Next()) {
279  // Check if this break point is closer that what was previously found.
280  if (it.code_offset() <= offset && offset - it.code_offset() < distance) {
281  closest_break = it.break_index();
282  distance = offset - it.code_offset();
283  // Check whether we can't get any closer.
284  if (distance == 0) break;
285  }
286  }
287  return closest_break;
288 }

290 bool BreakLocation::HasBreakPoint(Isolate* isolate,
291  Handle<DebugInfo> debug_info) const {
292  // First check whether there is a break point with the same source position.
293  if (!debug_info->HasBreakInfo() ||
294  !debug_info->HasBreakPoint(isolate, position_)) {
295  return false;
296  }
297  if (debug_info->CanBreakAtEntry()) {
298  DCHECK_EQ(Debug::kBreakAtEntryPosition, position_);
299  return debug_info->BreakAtEntry();
300  } else {
301  // Then check whether a break point at that source position would have
302  // the same code offset. Otherwise it's just a break location that we can
303  // step to, but not actually a location where we can put a break point.
304  DCHECK(IsBytecodeArray(*abstract_code_, isolate));
305  BreakIterator it(debug_info);
306  it.SkipToPosition(position_);
307  return it.code_offset() == code_offset_;
308  }
309 }

311 debug::BreakLocationType BreakLocation::type() const {
312  switch (type_) {
313  case DEBUGGER_STATEMENT:
314  return debug::kDebuggerStatementBreakLocation;
315  case DEBUG_BREAK_SLOT_AT_CALL:
316  return debug::kCallBreakLocation;
317  case DEBUG_BREAK_SLOT_AT_RETURN:
318  return debug::kReturnBreakLocation;
319 
320  // Externally, suspend breaks should look like normal breaks.
321  case DEBUG_BREAK_SLOT_AT_SUSPEND:
322  default:
323  return debug::kCommonBreakLocation;
324  }
325 }

328  : debug_info_(debug_info),
329  break_index_(-1),

331  debug_info->DebugBytecodeArray(Isolate::Current())
332  ->SourcePositionTable()) {

334  statement_position_ = position_;
335  // There is at least one break location.
336  DCHECK(!Done());
337  Next();
338 }
339 
340 int BreakIterator::BreakIndexFromPosition(int source_position) {
341  for (; !Done(); Next()) {
342  if (GetDebugBreakType() == DEBUG_BREAK_SLOT_AT_SUSPEND) continue;
343  if (source_position <= position()) {
344  int first_break = break_index();
345  for (; !Done(); Next()) {
346  if (GetDebugBreakType() == DEBUG_BREAK_SLOT_AT_SUSPEND) continue;
347  if (source_position == position()) return break_index();
348  }
349  return first_break;
350  }
351  }
352  return break_index();
353 }
354 
355 void BreakIterator::Next() {
356  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
357  DCHECK(!Done());
358  bool first = break_index_ == -1;
359  while (!Done()) {
360  if (!first) source_position_iterator_.Advance();
361  first = false;
362  if (Done()) return;
363  if (!source_position_iterator_.is_breakable()) continue;
364  position_ = source_position_iterator_.source_position().ScriptOffset();
365  if (source_position_iterator_.is_statement()) {
366  statement_position_ = position_;
367  }
368  DCHECK_LE(0, position_);
369  DCHECK_LE(0, statement_position_);
370 
371  DebugBreakType type = GetDebugBreakType();
372  if (type != NOT_DEBUG_BREAK) break;
373  }
374  break_index_++;
375 }
376 
377 DebugBreakType BreakIterator::GetDebugBreakType() {
378  Tagged<BytecodeArray> bytecode_array =
379  debug_info_->OriginalBytecodeArray(Isolate::Current());
380  interpreter::Bytecode bytecode =
381  interpreter::Bytecodes::FromByte(bytecode_array->get(code_offset()));
382 
383  // Make sure we read the actual bytecode, not a prefix scaling bytecode.
384  if (interpreter::Bytecodes::IsPrefixScalingBytecode(bytecode)) {
385  bytecode = interpreter::Bytecodes::FromByte(
386  bytecode_array->get(code_offset() + 1));
387  }
388 
389  if (bytecode == interpreter::Bytecode::kDebugger) {
390  return DEBUGGER_STATEMENT;
391  } else if (bytecode == interpreter::Bytecode::kReturn) {
392  return DEBUG_BREAK_SLOT_AT_RETURN;
393  } else if (bytecode == interpreter::Bytecode::kSuspendGenerator) {
394  // SuspendGenerator should always only carry an expression position that
395  // is used in stack trace construction, but should never be a breakable
396  // position reported to the debugger front-end.
397  DCHECK(!source_position_iterator_.is_statement());
398  return DEBUG_BREAK_SLOT_AT_SUSPEND;
399  } else if (interpreter::Bytecodes::IsCallOrConstruct(bytecode)) {
400  return DEBUG_BREAK_SLOT_AT_CALL;
401  } else if (source_position_iterator_.is_statement()) {
402  return DEBUG_BREAK_SLOT;
403  } else {
404  return NOT_DEBUG_BREAK;
405  }
406 }

408 void BreakIterator::SkipToPosition(int position) {
409  BreakIterator it(debug_info_);
410  SkipTo(it.BreakIndexFromPosition(position));
411 }

432 BreakLocation BreakIterator::GetBreakLocation() {
433  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
434  Handle<AbstractCode> code(
435  Cast<AbstractCode>(debug_info_->DebugBytecodeArray(isolate)), isolate);
436  DebugBreakType type = GetDebugBreakType();
437  int generator_object_reg_index = -1;
438  int generator_suspend_id = -1;
439  if (type == DEBUG_BREAK_SLOT_AT_SUSPEND) {
440  // For suspend break, we'll need the generator object to be able to step
441  // over the suspend as if it didn't return. We get the interpreter register
442  // index that holds the generator object by reading it directly off the
443  // bytecode array, and we'll read the actual generator object off the
444  // interpreter stack frame in GetGeneratorObjectForSuspendedFrame.
445  Tagged<BytecodeArray> bytecode_array =
446  debug_info_->OriginalBytecodeArray(isolate);
447  interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator iterator(handle(bytecode_array, isolate),
448  code_offset());
449 
450  DCHECK_EQ(iterator.current_bytecode(),
451  interpreter::Bytecode::kSuspendGenerator);
452  interpreter::Register generator_obj_reg = iterator.GetRegisterOperand(0);
453  generator_object_reg_index = generator_obj_reg.index();
454 
455  // Also memorize the suspend ID, to be able to decide whether
456  // we are paused on the implicit initial yield later.
457  generator_suspend_id = iterator.GetUnsignedImmediateOperand(3);
458  }
459  return BreakLocation(code, type, code_offset(), position_,
460  generator_object_reg_index, generator_suspend_id);
461 }

492 char* Debug::RestoreDebug(char* storage) {
493  MemCopy(reinterpret_cast<char*>(&thread_local_), storage,
494  ArchiveSpacePerThread());
495 
496  // Enter the isolate.
497  v8::Isolate::Scope isolate_scope(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(isolate_));
498  // Enter the debugger.
499  DebugScope debug_scope(this);
500 
501  // Clear any one-shot breakpoints that may have been set by the other
502  // thread, and reapply breakpoints for this thread.
503  ClearOneShot();
504 
505  if (thread_local_.last_step_action_ != StepNone) {
506  int current_frame_count = CurrentFrameCount();
507  int target_frame_count = thread_local_.target_frame_count_;
508  DCHECK(current_frame_count >= target_frame_count);
509  DebuggableStackFrameIterator frames_it(isolate_);
510  while (current_frame_count > target_frame_count) {
511  current_frame_count -= frames_it.FrameFunctionCount();
512  frames_it.Advance();
513  }
514  DCHECK(current_frame_count == target_frame_count);
515  // Set frame to what it was at Step break
516  thread_local_.break_frame_id_ = frames_it.frame()->id();
517 
518  // Reset the previous step action for this thread.
519  PrepareStep(thread_local_.last_step_action_);
520  }
521 
522  return storage + ArchiveSpacePerThread();
523 }

548 void DebugInfoCollection::Insert(Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi,

595 void DebugInfoCollection::DeleteIndex(size_t index) {
596  base::MutexGuard mutex_guard(isolate_->shared_function_info_access());
597 
598  Tagged<DebugInfo> debug_info = EntryAsDebugInfo(index);
599  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi = debug_info->shared();
600  DCHECK(Contains(sfi));
601 
602  auto it = map_.find(sfi->unique_id());
603  HandleLocation location = it->second;
604  DCHECK_EQ(location, list_[index]);
605  map_.erase(it);
606 
607  list_[index] = list_.back();
608  list_.pop_back();
609 
610  GlobalHandles::Destroy(location);
611  DCHECK(!Contains(sfi));
612  DCHECK_EQ(list_.size(), map_.size());
613 }

625 Debug::OnInstrumentationBreak() {

639 void Debug::Break(JavaScriptFrame* frame,
640  DirectHandle<JSFunction> break_target) {
641  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
642  // Just continue if breaks are disabled or debugger cannot be loaded.
643  if (break_disabled()) return;
644 
645  // Enter the debugger.
646  DebugScope debug_scope(this);
647  DisableBreak no_recursive_break(this);
648 
649  // Return if we fail to retrieve debug info.
650  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared(break_target->shared(), isolate_);
651  if (!EnsureBreakInfo(shared)) return;
652  PrepareFunctionForDebugExecution(shared);
653 
654  Handle<DebugInfo> debug_info(TryGetDebugInfo(*shared).value(), isolate_);
655 
656  // Find the break location where execution has stopped.
657  BreakLocation location = BreakLocation::FromFrame(debug_info, frame);
658  const bool hitInstrumentationBreak =
659  IsBreakOnInstrumentation(debug_info, location);
660  bool shouldPauseAfterInstrumentation = false;
661  if (hitInstrumentationBreak) {
662  debug::DebugDelegate::ActionAfterInstrumentation action =
663  OnInstrumentationBreak();
664  switch (action) {
665  case debug::DebugDelegate::ActionAfterInstrumentation::kPause:
666  shouldPauseAfterInstrumentation = true;
667  break;
668  case debug::DebugDelegate::ActionAfterInstrumentation::
669  kPauseIfBreakpointsHit:
670  shouldPauseAfterInstrumentation = false;
671  break;
672  case debug::DebugDelegate::ActionAfterInstrumentation::kContinue:
673  return;
674  }
675  }
676 
677  // Find actual break points, if any, and trigger debug break event.
678  ClearMutedLocation();
679  bool has_break_points;
680  bool scheduled_break =
681  scheduled_break_on_function_call() || shouldPauseAfterInstrumentation;
682  MaybeHandle<FixedArray> break_points_hit =
683  CheckBreakPoints(debug_info, &location, &has_break_points);
684  if (!break_points_hit.is_null() || break_on_next_function_call() ||
685  scheduled_break) {
686  StepAction lastStepAction = last_step_action();
687  debug::BreakReasons break_reasons;
688  if (scheduled_break) {
689  break_reasons.Add(debug::BreakReason::kScheduled);
690  }
691  // If it's a debugger statement, add the reason and then mute the location
692  // so we don't stop a second time.
693  bool is_debugger_statement = IsBreakOnDebuggerStatement(shared, location);
694  if (is_debugger_statement) {
695  break_reasons.Add(debug::BreakReason::kDebuggerStatement);
696  }
697 
698  // Clear all current stepping setup.
699  ClearStepping();
700  // Notify the debug event listeners.
701  OnDebugBreak(!break_points_hit.is_null()
702  ? break_points_hit.ToHandleChecked()
703  : isolate_->factory()->empty_fixed_array(),
704  lastStepAction, break_reasons);
705 
706  if (is_debugger_statement) {
707  // Don't pause here a second time
708  SetMutedLocation(shared, location);
709  }
710  return;
711  }
712 
713  // Debug break at function entry, do not worry about stepping.
714  if (location.IsDebugBreakAtEntry()) {
715  DCHECK(debug_info->BreakAtEntry());
716  return;
717  }
718 
719  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(frame);
720 
721  // No break point. Check for stepping.
722  StepAction step_action = last_step_action();
723  int current_frame_count = CurrentFrameCount();
724  int target_frame_count = thread_local_.target_frame_count_;
725  int last_frame_count = thread_local_.last_frame_count_;
726 
727  // StepOut at not return position was requested and return break locations
728  // were flooded with one shots.
729  if (thread_local_.fast_forward_to_return_) {
730  // We might hit an instrumentation breakpoint before running into a
731  // return/suspend location.
732  DCHECK(location.IsReturnOrSuspend() || hitInstrumentationBreak);
733  // We have to ignore recursive calls to function.
734  if (current_frame_count > target_frame_count) return;
735  ClearStepping();
736  PrepareStep(StepOut);
737  return;
738  }
739 
740  bool step_break = false;
741  switch (step_action) {
742  case StepNone:
743  if (has_break_points) {
744  SetMutedLocation(shared, location);
745  }
746  return;
747  case StepOut:
748  // StepOut should not break in a deeper frame than target frame.
749  if (current_frame_count > target_frame_count) return;
750  step_break = true;
751  break;
752  case StepOver:
753  // StepOver should not break in a deeper frame than target frame.
754  if (current_frame_count > target_frame_count) return;
755  [[fallthrough]];
756  case StepInto: {
757  // StepInto and StepOver should enter "generator stepping" mode, except
758  // for the implicit initial yield in generators, where it should simply
759  // step out of the generator function.
760  if (location.IsSuspend()) {
761  DCHECK(!has_suspended_generator());
762  ClearStepping();
763  if (!IsGeneratorFunction(shared->kind()) ||
764  location.generator_suspend_id() > 0) {
765  thread_local_.suspended_generator_ =
766  location.GetGeneratorObjectForSuspendedFrame(frame);
767  } else {
768  PrepareStep(StepOut);
769  }
770  return;
771  }
772  FrameSummary summary = FrameSummary::GetTop(frame);
773  const bool frame_or_statement_changed =
774  current_frame_count != last_frame_count ||
775  thread_local_.last_statement_position_ !=
776  summary.SourceStatementPosition();
777  // If we stayed on the same frame and reached the same bytecode offset
778  // since the last step, we are in a loop and should pause. Otherwise
779  // we keep "stepping" through the loop without ever actually pausing.
780  const bool potential_single_statement_loop =
781  current_frame_count == last_frame_count &&
782  thread_local_.last_bytecode_offset_ == summary.code_offset();
783  step_break = step_break || location.IsReturn() ||
784  potential_single_statement_loop ||
785  frame_or_statement_changed;
786  break;
787  }
788  }
789 
790  StepAction lastStepAction = last_step_action();
791  // Clear all current stepping setup.
792  ClearStepping();
793 
794  if (step_break) {
795  // If it's a debugger statement, add the reason and then mute the location
796  // so we don't stop a second time.
797  debug::BreakReasons break_reasons;
798  bool is_debugger_statement = IsBreakOnDebuggerStatement(shared, location);
799  if (is_debugger_statement) {
800  break_reasons.Add(debug::BreakReason::kDebuggerStatement);
801  }
802  // Notify the debug event listeners.
803  OnDebugBreak(isolate_->factory()->empty_fixed_array(), lastStepAction,
804  break_reasons);
805 
806  if (is_debugger_statement) {
807  // Don't pause here a second time
808  SetMutedLocation(shared, location);
809  }
810  } else {
811  // Re-prepare to continue.
812  PrepareStep(step_action);
813  }
814 }

816 bool Debug::IsBreakOnInstrumentation(Handle<DebugInfo> debug_info,
817  const BreakLocation& location) {
818  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
819  bool has_break_points_to_check =
820  break_points_active_ && location.HasBreakPoint(isolate_, debug_info);
821  if (!has_break_points_to_check) return {};
822 
823  DirectHandle<Object> break_points =
824  debug_info->GetBreakPoints(isolate_, location.position());
825  DCHECK(!IsUndefined(*break_points, isolate_));
826  if (!IsFixedArray(*break_points)) {
827  const auto break_point = Cast<BreakPoint>(break_points);
828  return break_point->id() == kInstrumentationId;
829  }
830 
831  DirectHandle<FixedArray> array(Cast<FixedArray>(*break_points), isolate_);
832  for (int i = 0; i < array->length(); ++i) {
833  const auto break_point =
834  Cast<BreakPoint>(direct_handle(array->get(i), isolate_));
835  if (break_point->id() == kInstrumentationId) {
836  return true;
837  }
838  }
839  return false;
840 }

842 bool Debug::IsBreakOnDebuggerStatement(
843  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> function, const BreakLocation& location) {
844  if (!function->HasBytecodeArray()) {
845  return false;
846  }
847  Tagged<BytecodeArray> original_bytecode =
848  function->GetBytecodeArray(isolate_);
849  interpreter::Bytecode bytecode = interpreter::Bytecodes::FromByte(
850  original_bytecode->get(location.code_offset()));
851  return bytecode == interpreter::Bytecode::kDebugger;
852 }
853 
854 // Find break point objects for this location, if any, and evaluate them.
855 // Return an array of break point objects that evaluated true, or an empty
856 // handle if none evaluated true.
857 // has_break_points will be true, if there is any (non-instrumentation)
858 // breakpoint.
859 MaybeHandle<FixedArray> Debug::CheckBreakPoints(Handle<DebugInfo> debug_info,
860  BreakLocation* location,
861  bool* has_break_points) {
862  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
863  bool has_break_points_to_check =
864  break_points_active_ && location->HasBreakPoint(isolate_, debug_info);
865  if (!has_break_points_to_check) {
866  *has_break_points = false;
867  return {};
868  }
869 
870  return Debug::GetHitBreakPoints(debug_info, location->position(),
871  has_break_points);
872 }

874 bool Debug::IsMutedAtAnyBreakLocation(
875  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> function,
876  const std::vector<BreakLocation>& locations) {
877  // A break location is considered muted if break locations on the current
878  // statement have at least one break point, and all of these break points
879  // evaluate to false. Aside from not triggering a debug break event at the
880  // break location, we also do not trigger one for debugger statements, nor
881  // an exception event on exception at this location.
882  // This should have been computed at last break, and we should just
883  // check that we are not at that location.
884 
885  if (IsSmi(thread_local_.muted_function_) ||
886  *function != thread_local_.muted_function_) {
887  return false;
888  }
889 
890  for (const BreakLocation& location : locations) {
891  if (location.position() == thread_local_.muted_position_) {
892  return true;
893  }
894  }
895 
896  return false;
897 }

923 // Check whether a single break point object is triggered.
924 bool Debug::CheckBreakPoint(DirectHandle<BreakPoint> break_point,
925  bool is_break_at_entry) {
926  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
927  HandleScope scope(isolate_);
928 
929  // Instrumentation breakpoints are handled separately.
930  if (break_point->id() == kInstrumentationId) {
931  return false;
932  }
933 
934  if (!break_point->condition()->length()) return true;
935  DirectHandle<String> condition(break_point->condition(), isolate_);
936  MaybeDirectHandle<Object> maybe_result;
937  DirectHandle<Object> result;
938 
939  if (is_break_at_entry) {
940  maybe_result = DebugEvaluate::WithTopmostArguments(isolate_, condition);
941  } else {
942  // Since we call CheckBreakpoint only for deoptimized frame on top of stack,
943  // we can use 0 as index of inlined frame.
944  const int inlined_jsframe_index = 0;
945  const bool throw_on_side_effect = false;
946  maybe_result =
947  DebugEvaluate::Local(isolate_, break_frame_id(), inlined_jsframe_index,
948  condition, throw_on_side_effect);
949  }
950 
951  DirectHandle<Object> maybe_exception;
952  bool exception_thrown = true;
953  if (maybe_result.ToHandle(&result)) {
954  exception_thrown = false;
955  } else if (isolate_->has_exception()) {
956  maybe_exception = direct_handle(isolate_->exception(), isolate_);
957  isolate_->clear_exception();
958  }
959 
960  CHECK(in_debug_scope());
961  DisableBreak no_recursive_break(this);
962 
963  {
964  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebuggerCallback);
965  debug_delegate_->BreakpointConditionEvaluated(
966  v8::Utils::ToLocal(isolate_->native_context()), break_point->id(),
967  exception_thrown, v8::Utils::ToLocal(maybe_exception));
968  }
969 
970  return !result.is_null() ? Object::BooleanValue(*result, isolate_) : false;
971 }

973 bool Debug::SetBreakpoint(Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared,
974  DirectHandle<BreakPoint> break_point,
975  int* source_position) {
976  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
977  HandleScope scope(isolate_);
978 
979  // Make sure the function is compiled and has set up the debug info.
980  if (!EnsureBreakInfo(shared)) return false;
981  PrepareFunctionForDebugExecution(shared);
982 
983  Handle<DebugInfo> debug_info(TryGetDebugInfo(*shared).value(), isolate_);
984  // Source positions starts with zero.
985  DCHECK_LE(0, *source_position);
986 
987  // Find the break point and change it.
988  *source_position = FindBreakablePosition(debug_info, *source_position);
989  DebugInfo::SetBreakPoint(isolate_, debug_info, *source_position, break_point);
990  // At least one active break point now.
991  DCHECK_LT(0, debug_info->GetBreakPointCount(isolate_));
992 
993  ClearBreakPoints(debug_info);
994  ApplyBreakPoints(debug_info);
995  return true;
996 }

998 bool Debug::SetBreakPointForScript(Handle<Script> script,
999  DirectHandle<String> condition,
1000  int* source_position, int* id) {
1001  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
1002  *id = ++thread_local_.last_breakpoint_id_;
1003  DirectHandle<BreakPoint> break_point =
1004  isolate_->factory()->NewBreakPoint(*id, condition);
1005 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1006  if (script->type() == Script::Type::kWasm) {
1007  RecordWasmScriptWithBreakpoints(script);
1008  return WasmScript::SetBreakPoint(script, source_position, break_point);
1009  }
1010 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1011 
1012  HandleScope scope(isolate_);
1013 
1014  // Obtain shared function info for the innermost function containing this
1015  // position.
1016  Handle<Object> result =
1017  FindInnermostContainingFunctionInfo(script, *source_position);
1018  if (IsUndefined(*result, isolate_)) return false;
1019 
1020  auto shared = Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(result);
1021  if (!EnsureBreakInfo(shared)) return false;
1022  PrepareFunctionForDebugExecution(shared);
1023 
1024  // Find the nested shared function info that is closest to the position within
1025  // the containing function.
1026  shared = FindClosestSharedFunctionInfoFromPosition(*source_position, script,
1027  shared);
1028 
1029  // Set the breakpoint in the function.
1030  return SetBreakpoint(shared, break_point, source_position);
1031 }

1033 int Debug::FindBreakablePosition(Handle<DebugInfo> debug_info,
1034  int source_position) {
1035  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
1036  if (debug_info->CanBreakAtEntry()) {
1037  return kBreakAtEntryPosition;
1038  } else {
1039  DCHECK(debug_info->HasInstrumentedBytecodeArray());
1040  BreakIterator it(debug_info);
1041  it.SkipToPosition(source_position);

1046 void Debug::ApplyBreakPoints(Handle<DebugInfo> debug_info) {
1047  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
1048  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1049  if (debug_info->CanBreakAtEntry()) {
1050  debug_info->SetBreakAtEntry();
1051  } else {
1052  if (!debug_info->HasInstrumentedBytecodeArray()) return;
1053  Tagged<FixedArray> break_points = debug_info->break_points();
1054  for (int i = 0; i < break_points->length(); i++) {
1055  if (IsUndefined(break_points->get(i), isolate_)) continue;
1056  Tagged<BreakPointInfo> info = Cast<BreakPointInfo>(break_points->get(i));
1057  if (info->GetBreakPointCount(isolate_) == 0) continue;
1058  DCHECK(debug_info->HasInstrumentedBytecodeArray());
1059  BreakIterator it(debug_info);
1060  it.SkipToPosition(info->source_position());
1061  it.SetDebugBreak();
1062  }
1063  }
1064  debug_info->SetDebugExecutionMode(DebugInfo::kBreakpoints);
1065 }

1067 void Debug::ClearBreakPoints(Handle<DebugInfo> debug_info) {
1068  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
1069  if (debug_info->CanBreakAtEntry()) {
1070  debug_info->ClearBreakAtEntry();
1071  } else {
1072  // If we attempt to clear breakpoints but none exist, simply return. This
1073  // can happen e.g. CoverageInfos exist but no breakpoints are set.
1074  if (!debug_info->HasInstrumentedBytecodeArray() ||
1075  !debug_info->HasBreakInfo()) {
1076  return;
1077  }
1078 
1079  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1080  for (BreakIterator it(debug_info); !it.Done(); it.Next()) {
1081  it.ClearDebugBreak();
1082  }
1083  }
1084 }

1086 void Debug::ClearBreakPoint(DirectHandle<BreakPoint> break_point) {
1087  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
1088  HandleScope scope(isolate_);
1089 
1090  DebugInfoCollection::Iterator it(&debug_infos_);
1091  for (; it.HasNext(); it.Advance()) {
1092  Handle<DebugInfo> debug_info(it.Next(), isolate_);
1093  if (!debug_info->HasBreakInfo()) continue;
1094 
1095  DirectHandle<Object> result =
1096  DebugInfo::FindBreakPointInfo(isolate_, debug_info, break_point);
1097  if (IsUndefined(*result, isolate_)) continue;
1098 
1099  if (DebugInfo::ClearBreakPoint(isolate_, debug_info, break_point)) {
1100  ClearBreakPoints(debug_info);
1101  if (debug_info->GetBreakPointCount(isolate_) == 0) {
1102  debug_info->ClearBreakInfo(isolate_);
1103  if (debug_info->IsEmpty()) it.DeleteNext();
1104  } else {
1105  ApplyBreakPoints(debug_info);
1106  }
1107  return;
1108  }
1109  }
1110 }

1180 void Debug::RecordWasmScriptWithBreakpoints(DirectHandle<Script> script) {
1181  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
1182  if (wasm_scripts_with_break_points_.is_null()) {
1183  DirectHandle<WeakArrayList> new_list =
1184  isolate_->factory()->NewWeakArrayList(4);
1185  wasm_scripts_with_break_points_ =
1186  isolate_->global_handles()->Create(*new_list);
1187  }
1188  {
1189  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1190  for (int idx = wasm_scripts_with_break_points_->length() - 1; idx >= 0;
1191  --idx) {
1192  Tagged<HeapObject> wasm_script;
1193  if (wasm_scripts_with_break_points_->Get(idx).GetHeapObject(
1194  &wasm_script) &&
1195  wasm_script == *script) {
1196  return;
1197  }
1198  }
1199  }
1200  DirectHandle<WeakArrayList> new_list =
1201  WeakArrayList::Append(isolate_, wasm_scripts_with_break_points_,
1202  MaybeObjectDirectHandle{script});
1203  if (*new_list != *wasm_scripts_with_break_points_) {
1204  isolate_->global_handles()->Destroy(
1205  wasm_scripts_with_break_points_.location());
1206  wasm_scripts_with_break_points_ =
1207  isolate_->global_handles()->Create(*new_list);
1208  }
1209 }

1212 // Clear out all the debug break code.
1213 void Debug::ClearAllBreakPoints() {
1214  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
1215  ClearAllDebugInfos([=, this](Handle<DebugInfo> info) {
1216  ClearBreakPoints(info);
1217  info->ClearBreakInfo(isolate_);
1218  });
1219 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY

1221  if (!wasm_scripts_with_break_points_.is_null()) {

1224  --idx) {

1227  &raw_wasm_script)) {

1229  WasmScript::ClearAllBreakpoints(wasm_script);
1230  wasm_script->wasm_native_module()->GetDebugInfo()->RemoveIsolate(
1231  isolate_);
1232  }

1234  wasm_scripts_with_break_points_ = Handle<WeakArrayList>{};
1235  }
1236 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY

1239 void Debug::FloodWithOneShot(Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared,
1240  bool returns_only) {
1241  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
1242  if (IsBlackboxed(shared)) return;
1243  // Make sure the function is compiled and has set up the debug info.
1244  if (!EnsureBreakInfo(shared)) return;
1245  PrepareFunctionForDebugExecution(shared);
1246 
1247  Handle<DebugInfo> debug_info(TryGetDebugInfo(*shared).value(), isolate_);
1248  // Flood the function with break points.
1249  DCHECK(debug_info->HasInstrumentedBytecodeArray());
1250  for (BreakIterator it(debug_info); !it.Done(); it.Next()) {
1251  if (returns_only && !it.GetBreakLocation().IsReturnOrSuspend()) continue;
1252  it.SetDebugBreak();
1253  }

1272 MaybeHandle<FixedArray> Debug::GetHitBreakPoints(
1273  DirectHandle<DebugInfo> debug_info, int position, bool* has_break_points) {
1274  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
1275  DirectHandle<Object> break_points =
1276  debug_info->GetBreakPoints(isolate_, position);
1277  bool is_break_at_entry = debug_info->BreakAtEntry();
1278  DCHECK(!IsUndefined(*break_points, isolate_));
1279  if (!IsFixedArray(*break_points)) {
1280  const auto break_point = Cast<BreakPoint>(break_points);
1281  *has_break_points = break_point->id() != kInstrumentationId;
1282  if (!CheckBreakPoint(break_point, is_break_at_entry)) {
1283  return {};
1284  }
1285  Handle<FixedArray> break_points_hit = isolate_->factory()->NewFixedArray(1);
1286  break_points_hit->set(0, *break_points);
1287  return break_points_hit;
1288  }
1289 
1290  DirectHandle<FixedArray> array(Cast<FixedArray>(*break_points), isolate_);
1291  int num_objects = array->length();
1292  Handle<FixedArray> break_points_hit =
1293  isolate_->factory()->NewFixedArray(num_objects);
1294  int break_points_hit_count = 0;
1295  *has_break_points = false;
1296  for (int i = 0; i < num_objects; ++i) {
1297  const auto break_point =
1298  Cast<BreakPoint>(direct_handle(array->get(i), isolate_));
1299  *has_break_points |= break_point->id() != kInstrumentationId;
1300  if (CheckBreakPoint(break_point, is_break_at_entry)) {
1301  break_points_hit->set(break_points_hit_count++, *break_point);
1302  }
1303  }
1304  if (break_points_hit_count == 0) return {};
1305  break_points_hit->RightTrim(isolate_, break_points_hit_count);
1306  return break_points_hit;
1307 }

1314  // function is called, then we will clear this flag and let stepping continue

1325 void Debug::PrepareStepIn(DirectHandle<JSFunction> function) {
1326  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
1327  CHECK(last_step_action() >= StepInto || break_on_next_function_call() ||
1328  scheduled_break_on_function_call());
1329  if (ignore_events()) return;
1330  if (in_debug_scope()) return;
1331  if (break_disabled()) return;
1332  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared(function->shared(), isolate_);
1333  if (IsBlackboxed(shared)) return;
1334  if (*function == thread_local_.ignore_step_into_function_) return;
1335  thread_local_.ignore_step_into_function_ = Smi::zero();
1336  FloodWithOneShot(shared);

1343  if (in_debug_scope()) return;

1348  Cast<JSGeneratorObject>(thread_local_.suspended_generator_)->function(),

1354 void Debug::PrepareStepOnThrow() {
1355  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
1356  if (last_step_action() == StepNone) return;
1357  if (ignore_events()) return;
1358  if (in_debug_scope()) return;
1359  if (break_disabled()) return;
1360 
1361  ClearOneShot();
1362 
1363  int current_frame_count = CurrentFrameCount();
1364 
1365  // Iterate through the JavaScript stack looking for handlers.
1366  JavaScriptStackFrameIterator it(isolate_);
1367  while (!it.done()) {
1368  JavaScriptFrame* frame = it.frame();
1369  if (frame->LookupExceptionHandlerInTable(nullptr, nullptr) > 0) break;
1370  std::vector<Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo>> infos;
1371  frame->GetFunctions(&infos);
1372  current_frame_count -= infos.size();
1373  it.Advance();
1374  }
1375 
1376  // No handler found. Nothing to instrument.
1377  if (it.done()) return;
1378 
1379  bool found_handler = false;
1380  // Iterate frames, including inlined frames. First, find the handler frame.
1381  // Then skip to the frame we want to break in, then instrument for stepping.
1382  for (; !it.done(); it.Advance()) {
1383  JavaScriptFrame* frame = JavaScriptFrame::cast(it.frame());
1384  if (last_step_action() == StepInto) {
1385  // Deoptimize frame to ensure calls are checked for step-in.
1386  Deoptimizer::DeoptimizeFunction(frame->function(),
1387  LazyDeoptimizeReason::kDebugger);
1388  }
1389  FrameSummaries summaries = frame->Summarize();
1390  for (size_t i = summaries.size(); i != 0; i--, current_frame_count--) {
1391  const FrameSummary& summary = summaries.frames[i - 1];
1392  if (!found_handler) {
1393  // We have yet to find the handler. If the frame inlines multiple
1394  // functions, we have to check each one for the handler.
1395  // If it only contains one function, we already found the handler.
1396  if (summaries.size() > 1) {
1397  DirectHandle<AbstractCode> code =
1398  summary.AsJavaScript().abstract_code();
1399  CHECK_EQ(CodeKind::INTERPRETED_FUNCTION, code->kind(isolate_));
1400  HandlerTable table(code->GetBytecodeArray());
1401  int code_offset = summary.code_offset();
1402  found_handler = table.LookupHandlerIndexForRange(code_offset) !=
1403  HandlerTable::kNoHandlerFound;
1404  } else {
1405  found_handler = true;
1406  }
1407  }
1408 
1409  if (found_handler) {
1410  // We found the handler. If we are stepping next or out, we need to
1411  // iterate until we found the suitable target frame to break in.
1412  if ((last_step_action() == StepOver || last_step_action() == StepOut) &&
1413  current_frame_count > thread_local_.target_frame_count_) {
1414  continue;
1415  }
1416  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> info(
1417  summary.AsJavaScript().function()->shared(), isolate_);
1418  if (IsBlackboxed(info)) continue;
1419  FloodWithOneShot(info);
1420  return;
1421  }
1422  }
1423  }
1424 }
1425 
1426 void Debug::PrepareStep(StepAction step_action) {
1427  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
1428  HandleScope scope(isolate_);
1429 
1430  DCHECK(in_debug_scope());
1431 
1432  // Get the frame where the execution has stopped and skip the debug frame if
1433  // any. The debug frame will only be present if execution was stopped due to
1434  // hitting a break point. In other situations (e.g. unhandled exception) the
1435  // debug frame is not present.
1436  StackFrameId frame_id = break_frame_id();
1437  // If there is no JavaScript stack don't do anything.
1438  if (frame_id == StackFrameId::NO_ID) return;
1439 
1440  thread_local_.last_step_action_ = step_action;
1441 
1442  DebuggableStackFrameIterator frames_it(isolate_, frame_id);
1443  CommonFrame* frame = frames_it.frame();
1444 
1445  BreakLocation location = BreakLocation::Invalid();
1446  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared;
1447  int current_frame_count = CurrentFrameCount();
1448 
1449  if (frame->is_javascript()) {
1450  JavaScriptFrame* js_frame = JavaScriptFrame::cast(frame);
1451  DCHECK(IsJSFunction(js_frame->function()));
1452 
1453  // Get the debug info (create it if it does not exist).
1454  auto summary = FrameSummary::GetTop(frame).AsJavaScript();
1455  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function(summary.function());
1456  shared = Handle<SharedFunctionInfo>(function->shared(), isolate_);
1457  if (!EnsureBreakInfo(shared)) return;
1458  PrepareFunctionForDebugExecution(shared);
1459 
1460  // PrepareFunctionForDebugExecution can invalidate Baseline frames
1461  js_frame = JavaScriptFrame::cast(frames_it.Reframe());
1462 
1463  Handle<DebugInfo> debug_info(TryGetDebugInfo(*shared).value(), isolate_);
1464  location = BreakLocation::FromFrame(debug_info, js_frame);
1465 
1466  // Any step at a return is a step-out, and a step-out at a suspend behaves
1467  // like a return.
1468  if (location.IsReturn() ||
1469  (location.IsSuspend() && step_action == StepOut)) {
1470  // On StepOut we'll ignore our further calls to current function in
1471  // PrepareStepIn callback.
1472  if (last_step_action() == StepOut) {
1473  thread_local_.ignore_step_into_function_ = *function;
1474  }
1475  step_action = StepOut;
1476  thread_local_.last_step_action_ = StepInto;
1477  }
1478 
1479  // We need to schedule DebugOnFunction call callback
1480  UpdateHookOnFunctionCall();
1481 
1482  // A step-next in blackboxed function is a step-out.
1483  if (step_action == StepOver && IsBlackboxed(shared)) step_action = StepOut;
1484 
1485  thread_local_.last_statement_position_ = summary.SourceStatementPosition();
1486  thread_local_.last_bytecode_offset_ = summary.code_offset();
1487  thread_local_.last_frame_count_ = current_frame_count;
1488  // No longer perform the current async step.
1489  clear_suspended_generator();
1490 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1491  } else if (frame->is_wasm() && step_action != StepOut) {
1492 #if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
1493  // TODO(paolosev@microsoft.com) - If we are running with the interpreter, we
1494  // cannot step.
1495  if (frame->is_wasm_interpreter_entry()) return;
1496 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
1497  // Handle stepping in wasm.
1498  WasmFrame* wasm_frame = WasmFrame::cast(frame);
1499  auto* debug_info = wasm_frame->native_module()->GetDebugInfo();
1500  if (debug_info->PrepareStep(wasm_frame)) {
1501  UpdateHookOnFunctionCall();
1502  return;
1503  }
1504  // If the wasm code is not debuggable or will return after this step
1505  // (indicated by {PrepareStep} returning false), then step out of that frame
1506  // instead.
1507  step_action = StepOut;
1508  UpdateHookOnFunctionCall();
1509 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1510  }
1511 
1512  switch (step_action) {
1513  case StepNone:
1514  UNREACHABLE();
1515  case StepOut: {
1516  // Clear last position info. For stepping out it does not matter.
1517  thread_local_.last_statement_position_ = kNoSourcePosition;
1518  thread_local_.last_bytecode_offset_ = kFunctionEntryBytecodeOffset;
1519  thread_local_.last_frame_count_ = -1;
1520  if (!shared.is_null()) {
1521  if (!location.IsReturnOrSuspend() && !IsBlackboxed(shared)) {
1522  // At not return position we flood return positions with one shots and
1523  // will repeat StepOut automatically at next break.
1524  thread_local_.target_frame_count_ = current_frame_count;
1525  thread_local_.fast_forward_to_return_ = true;
1526  FloodWithOneShot(shared, true);
1527  return;
1528  }
1529  if (IsAsyncFunction(shared->kind())) {
1530  // Stepping out of an async function whose implicit promise is awaited
1531  // by some other async function, should resume the latter. The return
1532  // value here is either a JSPromise or a JSGeneratorObject (for the
1533  // initial yield of async generators).
1534  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> return_value(
1535  Cast<JSReceiver>(thread_local_.return_value_), isolate_);
1536  DirectHandle<Object> awaited_by_holder = JSReceiver::GetDataProperty(
1537  isolate_, return_value,
1538  isolate_->factory()->promise_awaited_by_symbol());
1539  if (IsWeakFixedArray(*awaited_by_holder, isolate_)) {
1540  auto weak_fixed_array = Cast<WeakFixedArray>(awaited_by_holder);
1541  if (weak_fixed_array->length() == 1 &&
1542  weak_fixed_array->get(0).IsWeak()) {
1543  DirectHandle<HeapObject> awaited_by(
1544  weak_fixed_array->get(0).GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(isolate_),
1545  isolate_);
1546  if (IsJSGeneratorObject(*awaited_by)) {
1547  DCHECK(!has_suspended_generator());
1548  thread_local_.suspended_generator_ = *awaited_by;
1549  ClearStepping();
1550  return;
1551  }
1552  }
1553  }
1554  }
1555  }
1556  // Skip the current frame, find the first frame we want to step out to
1557  // and deoptimize every frame along the way.
1558  bool in_current_frame = true;
1559  for (; !frames_it.done(); frames_it.Advance()) {
1560 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1561 #if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
1562  // TODO(paolosev@microsoft.com): Implement stepping out from JS to wasm
1563  // interpreter.
1564  if (frame->is_wasm_interpreter_entry()) continue;
1565 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
1566  if (frames_it.frame()->is_wasm()) {
1567  if (in_current_frame) {
1568  in_current_frame = false;
1569  continue;
1570  }
1571  // Handle stepping out into Wasm.
1572  WasmFrame* wasm_frame = WasmFrame::cast(frames_it.frame());
1573  auto* debug_info = wasm_frame->native_module()->GetDebugInfo();
1574  if (debug_info->IsFrameBlackboxed(wasm_frame)) continue;
1575  debug_info->PrepareStepOutTo(wasm_frame);
1576  return;
1577  }
1578 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1579  JavaScriptFrame* js_frame = JavaScriptFrame::cast(frames_it.frame());
1580  if (last_step_action() == StepInto) {
1581  // Deoptimize frame to ensure calls are checked for step-in.
1582  Deoptimizer::DeoptimizeFunction(js_frame->function(),
1583  LazyDeoptimizeReason::kDebugger);
1584  }
1585  HandleScope inner_scope(isolate_);
1586  std::vector<Handle<SharedFunctionInfo>> infos;
1587  js_frame->GetFunctions(&infos);
1588  for (; !infos.empty(); current_frame_count--) {
1589  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> info = infos.back();
1590  infos.pop_back();
1591  if (in_current_frame) {
1592  // We want to step out, so skip the current frame.
1593  in_current_frame = false;
1594  continue;
1595  }
1596  if (IsBlackboxed(info)) continue;
1597  FloodWithOneShot(info);
1598  thread_local_.target_frame_count_ = current_frame_count;
1599  return;
1600  }
1601  }
1602  break;
1603  }
1604  case StepOver:
1605  thread_local_.target_frame_count_ = current_frame_count;
1606  [[fallthrough]];
1607  case StepInto:
1608  FloodWithOneShot(shared);
1609  break;
1610  }
1611 }

1613 // Simple function for returning the source positions for active break points.
1614 // static
1615 DirectHandle<Object> Debug::GetSourceBreakLocations(
1616  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared) {
1617  RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
1618  if (!shared->HasBreakInfo(isolate)) {
1619  return isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
1620  }
1621 
1622  DirectHandle<DebugInfo> debug_info(
1623  isolate->debug()->TryGetDebugInfo(*shared).value(), isolate);
1624  if (debug_info->GetBreakPointCount(isolate) == 0) {
1625  return isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
1626  }
1627  DirectHandle<FixedArray> locations = isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(
1628  debug_info->GetBreakPointCount(isolate));
1629  int count = 0;
1630  for (int i = 0; i < debug_info->break_points()->length(); ++i) {
1631  if (!IsUndefined(debug_info->break_points()->get(i), isolate)) {
1632  Tagged<BreakPointInfo> break_point_info =
1633  Cast<BreakPointInfo>(debug_info->break_points()->get(i));
1634  int break_points = break_point_info->GetBreakPointCount(isolate);
1635  if (break_points == 0) continue;
1636  for (int j = 0; j < break_points; ++j) {
1637  locations->set(count++,
1638  Smi::FromInt(break_point_info->source_position()));
1639  }
1640  }
1641  }
1642  return locations;
1643 }

1664 // Clears all the one-shot break points that are currently set. Normally this
1665 // function is called each time a break point is hit as one shot break points
1666 // are used to support stepping.
1667 void Debug::ClearOneShot() {
1668  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
1669  // The current implementation just runs through all the breakpoints. When the
1670  // last break point for a function is removed that function is automatically
1671  // removed from the list.

1674  for (; it.HasNext(); it.Advance()) {
1675  Handle<DebugInfo> debug_info(it.Next(), isolate_);

1677  ApplyBreakPoints(debug_info);
1678  }

1692 namespace {
1693 class DiscardBaselineCodeVisitor : public ThreadVisitor {
1694  public:
1695  explicit DiscardBaselineCodeVisitor(Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared)
1696  : shared_(shared) {}
1697  DiscardBaselineCodeVisitor() : shared_(SharedFunctionInfo()) {}
1698 
1699  void VisitThread(Isolate* isolate, ThreadLocalTop* top) override {
1700  DisallowGarbageCollection diallow_gc;
1701  bool deopt_all = shared_ == SharedFunctionInfo();
1702  for (JavaScriptStackFrameIterator it(isolate, top); !it.done();
1703  it.Advance()) {
1704  if (!deopt_all && it.frame()->function()->shared() != shared_) continue;
1705  if (it.frame()->type() != StackFrame::BASELINE &&
1706  it.frame()->type() != StackFrame::INTERPRETED) {
1707  continue;
1708  }
1709 
1710  Tagged<Code> code = it.frame()->LookupCode();
1711  // We need to check CodeKind rather than StackFrame type here since
1712  // previous iterations might already patched this baseline code,
1713  // but we need to update remaining baseline stack frames as well.
1714  if (code->kind() == CodeKind::BASELINE) {
1715  UnoptimizedJSFrame* frame = UnoptimizedJSFrame::cast(it.frame());
1716  int bytecode_offset = code->GetBytecodeOffsetForBaselinePC(
1717  frame->pc(), frame->GetBytecodeArray());
1718  Address* pc_addr = frame->pc_address();
1719  Address advance;
1720  if (bytecode_offset == kFunctionEntryBytecodeOffset) {
1721  advance = BUILTIN_CODE(isolate, BaselineOutOfLinePrologueDeopt)
1722  ->instruction_start();
1723  } else {
1724  advance = BUILTIN_CODE(isolate, InterpreterEnterAtNextBytecode)
1725  ->instruction_start();
1726  }
1727  if (v8_flags.cet_compatible) {
1728  Deoptimizer::PatchToJump(*pc_addr, advance);
1729  frame->LookupCode()->SetMarkedForDeoptimization(
1730  isolate, LazyDeoptimizeReason::kDebugger);
1731  } else {
1732  PointerAuthentication::ReplacePC(pc_addr, advance,
1733  kSystemPointerSize);
1734  }
1735  InterpretedFrame::cast(it.Reframe())
1736  ->PatchBytecodeOffset(bytecode_offset);
1737  }
1738  }
1739  }
1740 
1741  private:
1742  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_;
1743 };
1744 } // namespace
1745 
1746 void Debug::DiscardBaselineCode(Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared) {
1747  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
1748  DCHECK(shared->HasBaselineCode());
1749  DiscardBaselineCodeVisitor visitor(shared);
1750  visitor.VisitThread(isolate_, isolate_->thread_local_top());
1751  isolate_->thread_manager()->IterateArchivedThreads(&visitor);
1752  // TODO(v8:11429): Avoid this heap walk somehow.
1753  HeapObjectIterator iterator(isolate_->heap());
1754  auto trampoline = BUILTIN_CODE(isolate_, InterpreterEntryTrampoline);
1755  shared->FlushBaselineCode();
1756  for (Tagged<HeapObject> obj = iterator.Next(); !obj.is_null();
1757  obj = iterator.Next()) {
1758  if (IsJSFunction(obj)) {
1759  Tagged<JSFunction> fun = Cast<JSFunction>(obj);
1760  if (fun->shared() == shared && fun->ActiveTierIsBaseline(isolate_)) {
1761  fun->UpdateCode(isolate_, *trampoline);
1762  }
1763  }
1764  }
1765 }

1767 void Debug::DiscardAllBaselineCode() {
1768  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
1769  DiscardBaselineCodeVisitor visitor;
1770  visitor.VisitThread(isolate_, isolate_->thread_local_top());
1771  HeapObjectIterator iterator(isolate_->heap());
1772  auto trampoline = BUILTIN_CODE(isolate_, InterpreterEntryTrampoline);
1773  isolate_->thread_manager()->IterateArchivedThreads(&visitor);
1774  for (Tagged<HeapObject> obj = iterator.Next(); !obj.is_null();
1775  obj = iterator.Next()) {
1776  if (IsJSFunction(obj)) {
1777  Tagged<JSFunction> fun = Cast<JSFunction>(obj);
1778  if (fun->ActiveTierIsBaseline(isolate_)) {
1779  fun->UpdateCode(isolate_, *trampoline);
1780  }
1781  } else if (IsSharedFunctionInfo(obj)) {
1782  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(obj);
1783  if (shared->HasBaselineCode()) {
1784  shared->FlushBaselineCode();
1785  }
1786  }
1787  }
1788 }

1792

1794  DiscardBaselineCode(*shared);
1795  }

1799 void Debug::PrepareFunctionForDebugExecution(
1800  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared) {
1801  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
1802  // To prepare bytecode for debugging, we already need to have the debug
1803  // info (containing the debug copy) upfront, but since we do not recompile,
1804  // preparing for break points cannot fail.
1805  DCHECK(shared->is_compiled());
1806  DirectHandle<DebugInfo> debug_info(TryGetDebugInfo(*shared).value(),
1807  isolate_);
1808  if (debug_info->flags(kRelaxedLoad) & DebugInfo::kPreparedForDebugExecution) {
1809  return;
1810  }
1811 
1812  // Have to discard baseline code before installing debug bytecode, since the
1813  // bytecode array field on the baseline code object is immutable.
1814  if (debug_info->CanBreakAtEntry()) {
1815  // Deopt everything in case the function is inlined anywhere.
1816  Deoptimizer::DeoptimizeAll(isolate_);
1817  DiscardAllBaselineCode();
1818  } else {
1819  DeoptimizeFunction(shared);
1820  }
1821 
1822  if (shared->HasBytecodeArray()) {
1823  DCHECK(!shared->HasBaselineCode());
1824  SharedFunctionInfo::InstallDebugBytecode(shared, isolate_);
1825  }
1826 
1827  if (debug_info->CanBreakAtEntry()) {
1828  InstallDebugBreakTrampoline();
1829  } else {
1830  // Update PCs on the stack to point to recompiled code.
1831  RedirectActiveFunctions redirect_visitor(
1832  isolate_, *shared, RedirectActiveFunctions::Mode::kUseDebugBytecode);
1833  redirect_visitor.VisitThread(isolate_, isolate_->thread_local_top());
1834  isolate_->thread_manager()->IterateArchivedThreads(&redirect_visitor);
1835  }
1836 
1837  debug_info->set_flags(
1838  debug_info->flags(kRelaxedLoad) | DebugInfo::kPreparedForDebugExecution,
1839  kRelaxedStore);
1840 }

1844 bool IsJSFunctionAndNeedsTrampoline(Isolate* isolate,
1845  Tagged<Object> maybe_function) {
1846  if (!IsJSFunction(maybe_function)) return false;
1847  std::optional<Tagged<DebugInfo>> debug_info =
1848  isolate->debug()->TryGetDebugInfo(
1849  Cast<JSFunction>(maybe_function)->shared());
1850  return debug_info.has_value() && debug_info.value()->CanBreakAtEntry();
1851 }

1854 
1855 void Debug::InstallDebugBreakTrampoline() {
1856  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
1857  // Check the list of debug infos whether the debug break trampoline needs to
1858  // be installed. If that's the case, iterate the heap for functions to rewire
1859  // to the trampoline.
1860  // If there is a breakpoint at function entry, we need to install trampoline.
1861  bool needs_to_use_trampoline = false;
1862  // If there we break at entry to an api callback, we need to clear ICs.
1863  bool needs_to_clear_ic = false;
1864 
1865  DebugInfoCollection::Iterator it(&debug_infos_);
1866  for (; it.HasNext(); it.Advance()) {
1867  Tagged<DebugInfo> debug_info = it.Next();
1868  if (debug_info->CanBreakAtEntry()) {
1869  needs_to_use_trampoline = true;
1870  if (debug_info->shared()->IsApiFunction()) {
1871  needs_to_clear_ic = true;
1872  break;
1873  }
1874  }
1875  }
1876 
1877  if (!needs_to_use_trampoline) return;
1878 
1879  HandleScope scope(isolate_);
1880  DirectHandle<Code> trampoline = BUILTIN_CODE(isolate_, DebugBreakTrampoline);
1881  std::vector<Handle<JSFunction>> needs_compile;
1882  using AccessorPairWithContext =
1883  std::pair<Handle<AccessorPair>, Handle<NativeContext>>;
1884  std::vector<AccessorPairWithContext> needs_instantiate;
1885  {
1886  // Deduplicate {needs_instantiate} by recording all collected AccessorPairs.
1887  std::set<Tagged<AccessorPair>> recorded;
1888  HeapObjectIterator iterator(isolate_->heap());
1889  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1890  for (Tagged<HeapObject> obj = iterator.Next(); !obj.is_null();
1891  obj = iterator.Next()) {
1892  if (needs_to_clear_ic && IsFeedbackVector(obj)) {
1893  Cast<FeedbackVector>(obj)->ClearSlots(isolate_);
1894  continue;
1895  } else if (IsJSFunctionAndNeedsTrampoline(isolate_, obj)) {
1896  Tagged<JSFunction> fun = Cast<JSFunction>(obj);
1897  if (!fun->is_compiled(isolate_)) {
1898  needs_compile.push_back(handle(fun, isolate_));
1899  } else {
1900  fun->UpdateCode(isolate_, *trampoline);
1901  }
1902  } else if (IsJSObject(obj)) {
1903  Tagged<JSObject> object = Cast<JSObject>(obj);
1904  Tagged<DescriptorArray> descriptors =
1905  object->map()->instance_descriptors(kRelaxedLoad);
1906 
1907  for (InternalIndex i : object->map()->IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
1908  if (descriptors->GetDetails(i).kind() == PropertyKind::kAccessor) {
1909  Tagged<Object> value = descriptors->GetStrongValue(i);
1910  if (!IsAccessorPair(value)) continue;
1911 
1912  Tagged<AccessorPair> accessor_pair = Cast<AccessorPair>(value);
1913  if (!IsFunctionTemplateInfo(accessor_pair->getter()) &&
1914  !IsFunctionTemplateInfo(accessor_pair->setter())) {
1915  continue;
1916  }
1917  if (recorded.find(accessor_pair) != recorded.end()) continue;
1918 
1919  needs_instantiate.emplace_back(
1920  handle(accessor_pair, isolate_),
1921  handle(object->GetCreationContext().value(), isolate_));
1922  recorded.insert(accessor_pair);
1923  }
1924  }
1925  }
1926  }
1927  }
1928 
1929  // Forcibly instantiate all lazy accessor pairs to make sure that they
1930  // properly hit the debug break trampoline.
1931  for (AccessorPairWithContext tuple : needs_instantiate) {
1932  DirectHandle<AccessorPair> accessor_pair = tuple.first;
1933  DirectHandle<NativeContext> native_context = tuple.second;
1934  DirectHandle<Object> getter = AccessorPair::GetComponent(
1935  isolate_, native_context, accessor_pair, ACCESSOR_GETTER);
1936  if (IsJSFunctionAndNeedsTrampoline(isolate_, *getter)) {
1937  Cast<JSFunction>(getter)->UpdateCode(isolate_, *trampoline);
1938  }
1939 
1940  DirectHandle<Object> setter = AccessorPair::GetComponent(
1941  isolate_, native_context, accessor_pair, ACCESSOR_SETTER);
1942  if (IsJSFunctionAndNeedsTrampoline(isolate_, *setter)) {
1943  Cast<JSFunction>(setter)->UpdateCode(isolate_, *trampoline);
1944  }
1945  }
1946 
1947  // By overwriting the function code with DebugBreakTrampoline, which tailcalls
1948  // to shared code, we bypass CompileLazy. Perform CompileLazy here instead.
1949  for (DirectHandle<JSFunction> fun : needs_compile) {
1950  IsCompiledScope is_compiled_scope;
1951  Compiler::Compile(isolate_, fun, Compiler::CLEAR_EXCEPTION,
1952  &is_compiled_scope);
1953  DCHECK(is_compiled_scope.is_compiled());
1954  fun->UpdateCode(isolate_, *trampoline);
1955  }
1956 }

1958 namespace {
1959 void FindBreakablePositions(Handle<DebugInfo> debug_info, int start_position,
1960  int end_position,
1961  std::vector<BreakLocation>* locations) {
1962  DCHECK(debug_info->HasInstrumentedBytecodeArray());
1963  BreakIterator it(debug_info);
1964  while (!it.Done()) {
1965  if (it.GetDebugBreakType() != DEBUG_BREAK_SLOT_AT_SUSPEND &&
1966  it.position() >= start_position && it.position() < end_position) {
1967  locations->push_back(it.GetBreakLocation());
1968  }
1969  it.Next();
1970  }
1971 }

1973 bool CompileTopLevel(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Script> script,
1974  MaybeHandle<SharedFunctionInfo>* result = nullptr) {
1975  if (script->compilation_type() == Script::CompilationType::kEval ||
1976  script->is_wrapped()) {
1977  return false;
1978  }
1979  UnoptimizedCompileState compile_state;
1980  ReusableUnoptimizedCompileState reusable_state(isolate);
1981  UnoptimizedCompileFlags flags =
1982  UnoptimizedCompileFlags::ForScriptCompile(isolate, *script);
1983  flags.set_is_reparse(true);
1984  ParseInfo parse_info(isolate, flags, &compile_state, &reusable_state);
1985  IsCompiledScope is_compiled_scope;
1986  const MaybeHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> maybe_result =
1987  Compiler::CompileToplevel(&parse_info, script, isolate,
1988  &is_compiled_scope);
1989  if (maybe_result.is_null()) {
1990  if (isolate->has_exception()) {
1991  isolate->clear_exception();
1992  }
1993  return false;
1994  }
1995  if (result) *result = maybe_result;
1996  return true;
1997 }

2000 bool Debug::GetPossibleBreakpoints(Handle<Script> script, int start_position,
2001  int end_position, bool restrict_to_function,
2002  std::vector<BreakLocation>* locations) {
2003  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
2004  if (restrict_to_function) {
2005  Handle<Object> result =
2006  FindInnermostContainingFunctionInfo(script, start_position);
2007  if (IsUndefined(*result, isolate_)) return false;
2008 
2009  // Make sure the function has set up the debug info.
2010  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(result);
2011  if (!EnsureBreakInfo(shared)) return false;
2012  PrepareFunctionForDebugExecution(shared);
2013 
2014  Handle<DebugInfo> debug_info(TryGetDebugInfo(*shared).value(), isolate_);
2015  FindBreakablePositions(debug_info, start_position, end_position, locations);
2016  return true;
2017  }
2018 
2019  HandleScope scope(isolate_);
2020  std::vector<Handle<SharedFunctionInfo>> candidates;
2021  if (!FindSharedFunctionInfosIntersectingRange(script, start_position,
2022  end_position, &candidates)) {
2023  return false;
2024  }
2025  for (const auto& candidate : candidates) {
2026  CHECK(candidate->HasBreakInfo(isolate_));
2027  Handle<DebugInfo> debug_info(TryGetDebugInfo(*candidate).value(), isolate_);
2028  FindBreakablePositions(debug_info, start_position, end_position, locations);
2029  }
2030  return true;
2031 }

2033 class SharedFunctionInfoFinder {
2034  public:
2035  explicit SharedFunctionInfoFinder(int target_position)
2036  : current_start_position_(kNoSourcePosition),
2037  target_position_(target_position) {}
2038 
2039  void NewCandidate(Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared,
2040  Tagged<JSFunction> closure = JSFunction()) {
2041  if (!shared->IsSubjectToDebugging()) return;
2042  int start_position = shared->function_token_position();
2043  if (start_position == kNoSourcePosition) {
2044  start_position = shared->StartPosition();
2045  }
2046 
2047  if (start_position > target_position_) return;
2048  if (target_position_ >= shared->EndPosition()) {
2049  // The SharedFunctionInfo::EndPosition() is generally exclusive, but there
2050  // are assumptions in various places in the debugger that for script level
2051  // (toplevel function) there's an end position that is technically outside
2052  // the script. It might be worth revisiting the overall design here at
2053  // some point in the future.
2054  if (!shared->is_toplevel() || target_position_ > shared->EndPosition()) {
2055  return;
2056  }
2057  }
2058 
2059  if (!current_candidate_.is_null()) {
2060  if (current_start_position_ == start_position &&
2061  shared->EndPosition() == current_candidate_->EndPosition()) {
2062  // If we already have a matching closure, do not throw it away.
2063  if (!current_candidate_closure_.is_null() && closure.is_null()) return;
2064  // If a top-level function contains only one function
2065  // declaration the source for the top-level and the function
2066  // is the same. In that case prefer the non top-level function.
2067  if (!current_candidate_->is_toplevel() && shared->is_toplevel()) return;
2068  } else if (start_position < current_start_position_ ||
2069  current_candidate_->EndPosition() < shared->EndPosition()) {
2070  return;
2071  }
2072  }
2073 
2074  current_start_position_ = start_position;
2075  current_candidate_ = shared;
2076  current_candidate_closure_ = closure;
2077  }
2078 
2079  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> Result() { return current_candidate_; }
2080 
2081  Tagged<JSFunction> ResultClosure() { return current_candidate_closure_; }
2082 
2083  private:
2084  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> current_candidate_;
2085  Tagged<JSFunction> current_candidate_closure_;
2086  int current_start_position_;
2087  int target_position_;
2088  DISALLOW_GARBAGE_COLLECTION(no_gc_)
2089 };
2090 
2091 namespace {
2092 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> FindSharedFunctionInfoCandidate(
2093  int position, DirectHandle<Script> script, Isolate* isolate) {
2094  SharedFunctionInfoFinder finder(position);
2095  SharedFunctionInfo::ScriptIterator iterator(isolate, *script);
2096  for (Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> info = iterator.Next(); !info.is_null();
2097  info = iterator.Next()) {
2098  finder.NewCandidate(info);
2099  }
2100  return finder.Result();
2101 }

2104 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> Debug::FindClosestSharedFunctionInfoFromPosition(
2105  int position, Handle<Script> script,
2106  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> outer_shared) {
2107  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
2108  Handle<DebugInfo> outer_debug_info(TryGetDebugInfo(*outer_shared).value(),
2109  isolate_);
2110  CHECK(outer_debug_info->HasBreakInfo());
2111  int closest_position = FindBreakablePosition(outer_debug_info, position);
2112  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> closest_candidate = outer_shared;
2113  if (closest_position == position) return outer_shared;
2114 
2115  const int start_position = outer_shared->StartPosition();
2116  const int end_position = outer_shared->EndPosition();
2117  if (start_position == end_position) return outer_shared;
2118 
2119  if (closest_position == 0) closest_position = end_position;
2120  std::vector<Handle<SharedFunctionInfo>> candidates;
2121  // Find all shared function infos of functions that are intersecting from
2122  // the requested position until the end of the enclosing function.
2123  if (!FindSharedFunctionInfosIntersectingRange(
2124  script, position, closest_position, &candidates)) {
2125  return outer_shared;
2126  }
2127 
2128  for (auto candidate : candidates) {
2129  Handle<DebugInfo> debug_info(TryGetDebugInfo(*candidate).value(), isolate_);
2130  CHECK(debug_info->HasBreakInfo());
2131  const int candidate_position = FindBreakablePosition(debug_info, position);
2132  if (candidate_position >= position &&
2133  candidate_position < closest_position) {
2134  closest_position = candidate_position;
2135  closest_candidate = candidate;
2136  }
2137  if (closest_position == position) break;
2138  }
2139  return closest_candidate;
2140 }
2141 
2142 bool Debug::FindSharedFunctionInfosIntersectingRange(
2143  Handle<Script> script, int start_position, int end_position,
2144  std::vector<Handle<SharedFunctionInfo>>* intersecting_shared) {
2145  bool candidateSubsumesRange = false;
2146  bool triedTopLevelCompile = false;
2147 
2148  while (true) {
2149  std::vector<Handle<SharedFunctionInfo>> candidates;
2150  std::vector<IsCompiledScope> compiled_scopes;
2151  {
2152  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2153  SharedFunctionInfo::ScriptIterator iterator(isolate_, *script);
2154  for (Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> info = iterator.Next(); !info.is_null();
2155  info = iterator.Next()) {
2156  if (info->EndPosition() < start_position ||
2157  info->StartPosition() >= end_position) {
2158  continue;
2159  }
2160  candidateSubsumesRange |= info->StartPosition() <= start_position &&
2161  info->EndPosition() >= end_position;
2162  if (!info->IsSubjectToDebugging()) continue;
2163  if (!info->is_compiled() && !info->allows_lazy_compilation()) continue;
2164  candidates.push_back(i::handle(info, isolate_));
2165  }
2166  }
2167 
2168  if (!triedTopLevelCompile && !candidateSubsumesRange &&
2169  script->infos()->length() > 0) {
2170  MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared =
2171  GetTopLevelWithRecompile(script, &triedTopLevelCompile);
2172  if (shared.is_null()) return false;
2173  if (triedTopLevelCompile) continue;
2174  }
2175 
2176  bool was_compiled = false;
2177  for (const auto& candidate : candidates) {
2178  IsCompiledScope is_compiled_scope(candidate->is_compiled_scope(isolate_));
2179  if (!is_compiled_scope.is_compiled()) {
2180  // InstructionStream that cannot be compiled lazily are internal and not
2181  // debuggable.
2182  DCHECK(candidate->allows_lazy_compilation());
2183  if (!Compiler::Compile(isolate_, candidate, Compiler::CLEAR_EXCEPTION,
2184  &is_compiled_scope)) {
2185  return false;
2186  } else {
2187  was_compiled = true;
2188  }
2189  }
2190  DCHECK(is_compiled_scope.is_compiled());
2191  compiled_scopes.push_back(is_compiled_scope);
2192  if (!EnsureBreakInfo(candidate)) return false;
2193  PrepareFunctionForDebugExecution(candidate);
2194  }
2195  if (was_compiled) continue;
2196  *intersecting_shared = std::move(candidates);
2197  return true;
2198  }
2199  UNREACHABLE();
2200 }

2202 MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> Debug::GetTopLevelWithRecompile(
2203  Handle<Script> script, bool* did_compile) {
2204  DCHECK_LE(kFunctionLiteralIdTopLevel, script->infos()->length());
2205  Tagged<MaybeObject> maybeToplevel =
2206  script->infos()->get(kFunctionLiteralIdTopLevel);
2207  Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object;
2208  const bool topLevelInfoExists =
2209  maybeToplevel.GetHeapObject(&heap_object) && !IsUndefined(heap_object);
2210  if (topLevelInfoExists) {
2211  if (did_compile) *did_compile = false;
2212  return direct_handle(Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(heap_object), isolate_);
2213  }
2214 
2215  MaybeHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared;
2216  CompileTopLevel(isolate_, script, &shared);
2217  if (did_compile) *did_compile = true;
2218  return shared;
2219 }
2220 
2221 // We need to find a SFI for a literal that may not yet have been compiled yet,
2222 // and there may not be a JSFunction referencing it. Find the SFI closest to
2223 // the given position, compile it to reveal possible inner SFIs and repeat.
2224 // While we are at this, also ensure code with debug break slots so that we do
2225 // not have to compile a SFI without JSFunction, which is paifu for those that
2226 // cannot be compiled without context (need to find outer compilable SFI etc.)
2227 Handle<Object> Debug::FindInnermostContainingFunctionInfo(Handle<Script> script,
2228  int position) {
2229  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
2230  for (int iteration = 0;; iteration++) {
2231  // Go through all shared function infos associated with this script to
2232  // find the innermost function containing this position.
2233  // If there is no shared function info for this script at all, there is
2234  // no point in looking for it by walking the heap.
2235 
2236  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared;
2237  IsCompiledScope is_compiled_scope;
2238  {
2239  shared = FindSharedFunctionInfoCandidate(position, script, isolate_);
2240  if (shared.is_null()) {
2241  if (iteration > 0) break;
2242  // It might be that the shared function info is not available as the
2243  // top level functions are removed due to the GC. Try to recompile
2244  // the top level functions.
2245  const bool success = CompileTopLevel(isolate_, script);
2246  if (!success) break;
2247  continue;
2248  }
2249  // We found it if it's already compiled.
2250  is_compiled_scope = shared->is_compiled_scope(isolate_);
2251  if (is_compiled_scope.is_compiled()) {
2252  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_handle(shared, isolate_);
2253  // If the iteration count is larger than 1, we had to compile the outer
2254  // function in order to create this shared function info. So there can
2255  // be no JSFunction referencing it. We can anticipate creating a debug
2256  // info while bypassing PrepareFunctionForDebugExecution.
2257  if (iteration > 1) {
2258  CreateBreakInfo(shared_handle);
2259  }
2260  return shared_handle;
2261  }
2262  }
2263  // If not, compile to reveal inner functions.
2264  HandleScope scope(isolate_);
2265  // InstructionStream that cannot be compiled lazily are internal and not
2266  // debuggable.
2267  DCHECK(shared->allows_lazy_compilation());
2268  if (!Compiler::Compile(isolate_, handle(shared, isolate_),
2269  Compiler::CLEAR_EXCEPTION, &is_compiled_scope)) {
2270  break;
2271  }
2272  }
2273  return isolate_->factory()->undefined_value();
2274 }

2276 // Ensures the debug information is present for shared.
2277 bool Debug::EnsureBreakInfo(Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared) {
2278  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
2279  // Return if we already have the break info for shared.
2280  if (shared->HasBreakInfo(isolate_)) {
2281  DCHECK(shared->is_compiled());
2282  return true;
2283  }
2284  if (!shared->IsSubjectToDebugging() && !CanBreakAtEntry(shared)) {
2285  return false;
2286  }
2287  IsCompiledScope is_compiled_scope = shared->is_compiled_scope(isolate_);
2288  if (!is_compiled_scope.is_compiled() &&
2289  !Compiler::Compile(isolate_, shared, Compiler::CLEAR_EXCEPTION,
2290  &is_compiled_scope, CreateSourcePositions::kYes)) {
2291  return false;
2292  }
2293  CreateBreakInfo(shared);
2294  return true;
2295 }

2332 void Debug::InstallCoverageInfo(DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared,
2333  DirectHandle<CoverageInfo> coverage_info) {
2334  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);

2449 std::optional<Tagged<Object>> Debug::OnThrow(DirectHandle<Object> exception) {
2450  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
2451  if (in_debug_scope() || ignore_events()) return {};
2452  // Temporarily clear any exception to allow evaluating
2453  // JavaScript from the debug event handler.
2454  HandleScope scope(isolate_);
2455  {
2456  std::optional<Isolate::ExceptionScope> exception_scope;
2457  if (isolate_->has_exception()) exception_scope.emplace(isolate_);
2458  Isolate::CatchType catch_type = isolate_->PredictExceptionCatcher();
2459  OnException(exception, MaybeDirectHandle<JSPromise>(),
2460  catch_type == Isolate::CAUGHT_BY_ASYNC_AWAIT ||
2461  catch_type == Isolate::CAUGHT_BY_PROMISE
2462  ? v8::debug::kPromiseRejection
2463  : v8::debug::kException);
2464  }
2465  PrepareStepOnThrow();
2466  // If the OnException handler requested termination, then indicated this to
2467  // our caller Isolate::Throw so it can deal with it immediately instead of
2468  // throwing the original exception.
2469  if (isolate_->stack_guard()->CheckTerminateExecution()) {
2470  isolate_->stack_guard()->ClearTerminateExecution();
2471  return isolate_->TerminateExecution();
2472  }
2473  return {};
2474 }

2501 
2502 void Debug::OnException(DirectHandle<Object> exception,
2503  MaybeDirectHandle<JSPromise> promise,
2504  v8::debug::ExceptionType exception_type) {
2505  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebugger);
2506  // Do not trigger exception event on stack overflow. We cannot perform
2507  // anything useful for debugging in that situation.
2508  StackLimitCheck stack_limit_check(isolate_);
2509  if (stack_limit_check.JsHasOverflowed()) return;
2510 
2511  // Return if the event has nowhere to go.
2512  if (!debug_delegate_) return;
2513 
2514  // Return if we are not interested in exception events.
2515  if (!break_on_caught_exception_ && !break_on_uncaught_exception_) return;
2516 
2517  HandleScope scope(isolate_);
2518 
2519  bool all_frames_ignored = true;
2520  bool is_debuggable = false;
2521  bool uncaught = !isolate_->WalkCallStackAndPromiseTree(
2522  promise, [this, &all_frames_ignored,
2523  &is_debuggable](Isolate::PromiseHandler handler) {
2524  if (!handler.async) {
2525  is_debuggable = true;
2526  } else if (!is_debuggable) {
2527  // Don't bother checking ignore listing if there are no debuggable
2528  // frames on the callstack
2529  return;
2530  }
2531  all_frames_ignored =
2532  all_frames_ignored &&
2533  IsBlackboxed(direct_handle(handler.function_info, isolate_));
2534  });
2535 
2536  if (all_frames_ignored || !is_debuggable) {
2537  return;
2538  }
2539 
2540  if (!uncaught) {
2541  if (!break_on_caught_exception_) {
2542  return;
2543  }
2544  } else {
2545  if (!break_on_uncaught_exception_) {
2546  return;
2547  }
2548  }
2549 
2550  {
2551  StackFrameIterator it(isolate_);
2552  for (; !it.done(); it.Advance()) {
2553  if (it.frame()->is_javascript()) {
2554  JavaScriptFrame* frame = JavaScriptFrame::cast(it.frame());
2555  FrameSummary summary = FrameSummary::GetTop(frame);
2556  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared{
2557  summary.AsJavaScript().function()->shared(), isolate_};
2558  if (shared->IsSubjectToDebugging()) {
2559  Handle<DebugInfo> debug_info;
2560  std::vector<BreakLocation> break_locations;
2561  if (ToHandle(isolate_, TryGetDebugInfo(*shared), &debug_info) &&
2562  debug_info->HasBreakInfo()) {
2563  // Enter the debugger.
2564  DebugScope debug_scope(this);
2565  BreakLocation::AllAtCurrentStatement(debug_info, frame,
2566  &break_locations);
2567  }
2568  if (IsMutedAtAnyBreakLocation(shared, break_locations)) {
2569  return;
2570  }
2571  break; // Stop at first debuggable function
2572  }
2573 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2574  } else if (it.frame()->is_wasm()) {
2575  const WasmFrame* frame = WasmFrame::cast(it.frame());
2576  if (IsMutedAtWasmLocation(frame->script(), frame->position())) {
2577  return;
2578  }
2579  // Wasm is always subject to debugging
2580  break;
2581 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2582  }
2583  }
2584 
2585  if (it.done()) return; // Do not trigger an event with an empty stack.
2586  }
2587 
2588  DebugScope debug_scope(this);
2589  DisableBreak no_recursive_break(this);
2590 
2591  {
2592  DirectHandle<Object> promise_object;
2593  if (!promise.ToHandle(&promise_object)) {
2594  promise_object = isolate_->factory()->undefined_value();
2595  }
2596  RCS_SCOPE(isolate_, RuntimeCallCounterId::kDebuggerCallback);
2597  debug_delegate_->ExceptionThrown(
2598  v8::Utils::ToLocal(isolate_->native_context()),
2599  v8::Utils::ToLocal(exception), v8::Utils::ToLocal(promise_object),
2600  uncaught, exception_type);
2601  }
2602 }
